{"agent_id":"D21a","type":"composite","name":"hook-warning-lifecycle-workflow","path":"scripts/","scope":"universal","portability":"portable","status":"active","purpose":"Cross-session hook warning persistence system: append-hook-warning.js writes new warnings to hook-warnings.json; sync-warnings-ack.js reconciles acknowledgments from hook-warnings-ack.json; the pre-push escalation gate blocks push if unacknowledged error-severity warnings exist.","dependencies":["append-hook-warning.js","sync-warnings-ack.js","hook-warnings.json","hook-warnings-ack.json","hook-warnings-log.jsonl",".husky/pre-push","block-push-to-main.js","check-remote-session-context.js","decision-save-prompt.js","governance-logger.js","deploy-safeguard.js","run-alerts.js"],"external_refs":[],"lineage":{"source_project":"sonash","source_path":"scripts/append-hook-warning.js","source_version":"current","ported_date":null},"sanitize_fields":[],"notes":"append-hook-warning.js is the hub utility called by 4+ hooks (check-remote-session-context, decision-save-prompt, governance-logger, deploy-safeguard) via execFileSync. The .claude/hook-warnings.json is the live warning store; hook-warnings-ack.json is the acknowledgment journal. The pre-push escalation gate (inline Node.js in .husky/pre-push) reads hook-warnings.json to block push on unacknowledged errors. sync-warnings-ack.js reconciles the two files. alerts skill reads hook-warnings-ack.json for its hook-warning category. run-alerts.js reads both files for suppression logic. JASON-OS port status: PARTIALLY PORTED — append-hook-warning.js and the state files exist in JASON-OS; sync-warnings-ack.js status unclear.","component_units":[{"name":"append-hook-warning.js","path":"scripts/append-hook-warning.js","role":"entry-point","type":"script"},{"name":"sync-warnings-ack.js","path":"scripts/sync-warnings-ack.js","role":"entry-point","type":"script"},{"name":"hook-warnings.json","path":".claude/hook-warnings.json","role":"state-file","type":"config"},{"n